cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper primarily focuses on security mechanisms for protecting against control-flow hijacking attacks, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the implementation and deployment of shadow stacks, which is a software engineering technique for improving program security. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the use of shadow stacks in C/C++ programs, which are programming languages that are prone to control-flow hijacking attacks. 
4. cs.AR (Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance overhead of different shadow stack designs on modern architectures, which falls under the domain of computer architecture. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of shadow stacks as a mechanism for controlling the flow of execution in programs, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
